%S A394555 36,484,1800,7396,13689,43681,1865956,27379323,29833444,554367025,
%T A394555 1938024529,3627816200,7635613924,7838092089,40903720200,122168424676,
%U A394555 188731633500,564067089936,9574460449352,20812245457936,31275004868836
%N A394555 Powerful k such that rad(Sum({m <= k : rad(m) = rad(k)})) = rad(k), where rad = A007947.
%C A394555 Intersection of A001694 and A393919.
%C A394555 Most numbers k such that rad(Sum({m <= k : rad(m) = rad(k)})) = rad(k) are in A332785 (i.e., neither powerful nor squarefree). Powerful terms in A393919 are rare.
%C A394555 Does not intersect A246547 (perfect powers of primes).
%C A394555 No intersection with A383394(1)..A383394(302010) (i.e., none less than 2^46), where A383394 is the list of perfect powers of Achilles numbers (in A052486).
%C A394555 No intersection with A052486(1)^2..A052486(300000)^2.
%C A394555 For p^6*q^4 from A6881(n) = p*q, primes, no intersection for n = 1..2^20.
%C A394555 Conjecture: this sequence intersects A383394.
%e A394555 Table of n, s(i), a(n) for n = 1..21, where s = A001694:
%e A394555    n Subset                     a(n)
%e A394555   -----------------------------------------------------------------
